A4.text: Tbilisi is the capital and largest city of Georgia

A5.text: After the Russian Revolution of 1917, the city served as a location of the Transcaucasus interim government which established, in the spring of 1918, the short-lived independent Transcaucasian Federation with the capital in Tbilisi.
